-- Forty-Three Firms With China Operations Prepare to Sell Shares in Taiwan
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-16T07:45:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-16/forty-three-firms-with-china-operations-prepare-to-sell-shares-in-taiwan.html
Forty-three companies with major
operations in China are receiving listing guidelines in
preparation to sell shares in Taiwan, Stanley Chu, deputy
general manager at Taiwan Stock Exchange Corp., said at a
conference in Shanghai today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
